= Categories of Tawḥīd

Tawḥīd can be divided into three categories:

1. _Tawḥīd al-Rubūbīyah_ -- Lordship (His actions)
2. _Tawḥīd al-Ulūhīyah_ -- Worship (pertains to action of slaves)
3. _Tawḥīd al-Asmāʾ wa al-Ṣifāt_ -- His Names and Attributes

(Details for each are as follows.)#footnote[The details were originally in table form, but the section on evidences would be difficult to read if it included both the Arabic _āyāt_ and their translations.]
// Here is a table with definitions of each category and their evidences:


== Tawḥīd al-Rubūbīyah

=== Definition

Singling out Allāh the Most High in:
1. Ownership
2. Creation
3. Administration/governing

...or we can say it's singling out Allāh in His actions such as Creating,
Providing sustenance, Giving and Taking life, Sending rain, etc.

=== Evidences

#quran-block[
أَلَا لَهُ ٱلۡخَلۡقُ وَٱلۡأَمۡرُۗ
][
His is the Creation and the command (Al-Aʿrāf, Q7:54)
]

#quran-block[
وَلِلَّهِ مُلۡكُ ٱلسَّمَٰوَٰتِ وَٱلۡأَرۡضِۗ
][
And to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth. (Āl ʿImrān, Q3:189)
]

#quran-block[
قُلۡ مَن يَرۡزُقُكُم مِّنَ ٱلسَّمَآءِ وَٱلۡأَرۡضِ أَمَّن يَمۡلِكُ ٱلسَّمۡعَ وَٱلۡأَبۡصَٰرَ وَمَن يُخۡرِجُ ٱلۡحَيَّ مِنَ ٱلۡمَيِّتِ وَيُخۡرِجُ ٱلۡمَيِّتَ مِنَ ٱلۡحَيِّ وَمَن يُدَبِّرُ ٱلۡأَمۡرَۚ فَسَيَقُولُونَ ٱللَّهُۚ فَقُلۡ أَفَلَا تَتَّقُونَ ٣١
][
Say, “Who provides for you from the heaven and the earth? Or who controls
hearing and sight and who brings the living out of the dead and brings the dead
out of the living and who arranges [every] matter?” They will say, “Allāh,” so
say, “Then will you not fear Him?” (Yūnus, Q10:31)
]


== Tawḥīd al-Ulūhīyah

=== Definition

Singling out Allāh the most High in the actions of His slaves (our actions),
e.g. Prayer, fasting, pilgrimage, reliance, hope, fear, love, etc.

=== Evidences

#quran-block[
وَمَا خَلَقۡتُ ٱلۡجِنَّ وَٱلۡإِنسَ إِلَّا لِيَعۡبُدُونِ ٥٦
][
And I have not created the Jinnkind and the mankind except for my worship. (al-Dhāriyāt, Q51:56)
]

#quran-block[
وَٱعۡبُدُواْ ٱللَّهَ وَلَا تُشۡرِكُواْ بِهِۦ شَيۡـٔٗاۖ
][
And worship Allāh alone and do not associate anything with Him. (al-Nisāʾ, Q4:36)
]

#quran-block[
وَمَآ أَرۡسَلۡنَا مِن قَبۡلِكَ مِن رَّسُولٍ إِلَّا نُوحِيٓ إِلَيۡهِ أَنَّهُۥ لَآ إِلَٰهَ إِلَّآ أَنَا۠ فَٱعۡبُدُونِ ٢٥
][
And We sent not before you any messenger except We revealed to him that, “There
is no deity except Me, so worship Me.” (Al-Anbiyāʾ, Q21:25)
]


== Tawḥīd al-Asmāʾ wa al-Ṣifāt

=== Definition

It's that Allāh be described with whatever He and His Prophet #pbuh has
described Him with, from the characteristics of perfection and qualities of
majesty without discussing how or in what manner the attributes are, without
likening Him to His creation, and without distortion (interpreting them in a way
different from the apparent meaning) and without denying any of His attributes.
(Majmūʿ al-Fatāwá Ibn ʿUthaymīn)

=== Evidences

#quran-block[
لَيۡسَ كَمِثۡلِهِۦ شَيۡءٞۖ وَهُوَ ٱلسَّمِيعُ ٱلۡبَصِيرُ ١١
][
There is nothing like unto Him and He is the All-Hearing, the All-Seeing. (Al-Shūrá, Q42:11)
]

#quran-block[
وَلِلَّهِ ٱلۡأَسۡمَآءُ ٱلۡحُسۡنَىٰ فَٱدۡعُوهُ بِهَاۖ وَذَرُواْ ٱلَّذِينَ يُلۡحِدُونَ فِيٓ أَسۡمَٰٓئِهِۦۚ سَيُجۡزَوۡنَ مَا كَانُواْ يَعۡمَلُونَ ١٨٠
][
And to Allāh belong the best names, so invoke Him by them. And leave those who
practice deviation concerning His names. They will be recompensed for what they
have been doing. (al-Aʿrāf, Q7:180)
]

